- skill: persistent_memory
  version: "1.0"
  trigger: always  # runs every session, no explicit invocation needed
  priority: CRITICAL  # must run before any other skill
  description: >
    Load and maintain the project's persistent memory system located in .memory/.
    This provides cross-session continuity of context, decisions, and state.
  boot_actions:
    - read: .memory/AGENT_MEMORY.md
    - read: .memory/SESSION_LOG.md
    - read: .memory/DECISIONS.md
    - read: .memory/TECH_CONTEXT.md
    - read: .memory/TODO.md
  shutdown_actions:
    - write_session_summary: .memory/SESSION_LOG.md
    - update_memory: .memory/AGENT_MEMORY.md
    - persist_decisions: .memory/DECISIONS.md
    - update_todos: .memory/TODO.md
  rules:
    - "Never skip the boot sequence, even for trivial tasks"
    - "Always confirm memory load in first response"
    - "Always confirm memory write in final response"
    - "Prune AGENT_MEMORY.md if it exceeds 500 lines"
    - "Flag decision conflicts rather than silently overriding"
